l = [10,20,30]

this will not work func1(l)

but we can unpack the list first and then pass it to the function
func1(*l) -> a=10, b=20, c=30

how boolean and work: !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
def avg(*args):
  count=len(args)
  total=sum(args)
  return count and total/count *********************************

def avg(*args):
  count=len(args)
  total=sum(args)
  if count == 0:
    return 0
  else:
    return total/count
    
